'''Ch<U+00E2>teau Belgrave''' is a [[winery]] in the [[Haut-M<U+00E9>doc]] [[Appellation d'Origine Contr<U+00F4>l<U+00E9>e|appellation]] of the [[Bordeaux]] region of [[France]]. The wine produced here was classified as one of eighteen ''Cinqui<U+00E8>mes Crus'' (Fifth Growths) in the [[Bordeaux Wine Official Classification of 1855]]. <ref> Karen MacNeil, ''The Wine Bible'' Workman Publishing 2001 pg. 885 ISBN 1-56305-434-5 </ref>

